   <taskbody>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Connect your laptop to the service port (J223) located
on the front side of the controller box.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <note class="- topic/note ">Use the service port cable 940â€“0024D for the
proper connection of all required signals.</note>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Launch the UPS Tuner, click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Next</uicontrol> , select <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Controller Box</uicontrol> and click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Next</uicontrol>.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Type <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">1</b> followed by the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Enter</uicontrol> key to open <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">System Information</uicontrol>.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Type <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">3</b> followed by the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Enter</uicontrol> key to open the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Eventlog</uicontrol>. The first 20 events
will now be displayed. To view all events, type <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">2</b> followed
by the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Enter</uicontrol> key.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">When the logs have finished loading into the terminal window,
the event logs can be filtered.</stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the bottom of the UPS Tuner window, click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Event Log Viewer</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">The event logs can now be filtered by module, date, event
type or event description for an easy overview of a single alarm.<p class="- topic/p "/>
               <p class="- topic/p "/>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
